Luck had nothing to do with crossing my 2nd Marathon finish line 🏁🥹.

It was the hard work.
The many half marathon races. 
The 300+ miles.
The sweat, tears, & blood.
The consistently showing up, even when it was tough. 
The many hours of cross training 🏋🏽‍♀️🚴🏽‍♀️🧘🏽‍♀️.

✨ The never giving up. ✨ 

You guys 🥹, I beat my time by 23 minutes from first Marathon last year and I didn’t hit a wall this time around! I felt great the entire time and even managed to keep a 9.30ish/mile pace.

My mindset was stronger this time because I knew what to expect and I was ready for it. I knew how it would feel, but I also knew that I had done it once, which meant I could do it again and I DID 🥇😭!

Today I realized that it takes a powerful village to make it all possible. The sideline hype squads 📣, the volunteers, the police officers, the encouraging DM 📥 messages, our friends and family. We are the ones crossing the finish line 🏁, but we couldn’t do it without you all. Thank you 🙏🏽 to everyone who makes this possible. 

Two down 🏃🏽‍♀️✔️ ….maybe more to come 🤷🏽‍♀️. Ask me once my legs 🦵🏽 stop throbbing and I’m able to walk normal😝.

They do become addicting don’t they?

My one advice to anyone who’s wanting to change their life is: make —CONSISTENCY —your superpower 🦸🏽‍♀️. 

Let go of the “all or nothing mentally” & just focus on creating a consistent 🔑 lifestyle. One day at a time. 

It won’t ever be perfect, so also let go of that unrealistic expectation and remember that imperfect action is better than no action. You’re allowed to make tweaks to fit into YOUR lifestyle, which will make this sustainable. 

I set out to run 🏃🏽‍♀️ 12 Half Marathons & one full Marathon 🥇 this year and I am proud to say that I 👏🏽 DID 👏🏽 THAT 👏🏽 .

I showed up everyday this year (minus rest days), whether we were in Durango Mexico 🇲🇽, Broken Bow Oklahoma 🏕️, Arizona, Missouri, Kansas City, Florida 🏝️, or at home 🏠 and gave it my BEST.

I have made consistency my superpower 🦸🏽‍♀️ & that’s what has allowed me to create a healthy, strong 💪🏽 , and empowering lifestyle and it can do the same for you. 

I challenge you to make “consistency” your word for 2023 💥. It will change your life.

Don’t fall into the “I’ll start next Monday” trap 🪤 ❌!

I get it, it’s easy to stay comfortable in the cozy “comfort zone”. I’ve been guilty of it too from time to time. It’s our human nature to seek and want easy and comfort. 

But, what I’ve found is that nothing meaningful ever grows 🌱 in that comfort zone. We find ourselves feeling stuck on that merry-go-round 🎠of unhappy, unhealthy, and just meh 😑 with life. Anyone feel this way right now?

We are simply a product of our daily choices (or lack of).

This doesn’t have to be complicated. It can be as simple as ⬇️:⁣
⁣
•You make the decision that you’re ready to change your life.⁣ It will never be “convenient”, so stop 🛑 waiting for that. 
•You choose a day. Mondays are always great, but not needed❌.
•You choose a fitness plan. ⁣
•You choose a nutrition 🥗program because nutrition is key 🔑. ⁣
•You allow yourself to be a beginner as you get better & stronger in the process. ⁣
•You take it one day at a time. ⁣
•You show up daily to flex 💪🏽 your discipline muscle & make consistency your superpower 🦸🏽‍♀️. ⁣
⁣
The rest will fall into place. All you gotta do is be willing to show up & focus on improving.
